Task: Jewellery Shop Item Logger
Goal: Write a Java program that lets you add jewellery item details to a file and read them back — simulating a simple inventory log.

What You'll Practice
Writing to a file using FileWriter / BufferedWriter

Reading from a file using FileReader / BufferedReader

Appending data without overwriting

Exception handling with try-catch

Task Requirements
Write item details (name, quantity, price) to a file called inventory.txt

Append new items without deleting old ones

Read and display all items from the file

Count the total number of items stored

Bonus Challenges 🚀
Once you finish the basic task, try these extensions:

Search for an item by name in the file

Delete a specific item from the file (rewrite without that line)

Sort items by price when reading

Export inventory as CSV format (useful for your shop app later!)